A disbarred Eastern Cape attorney has been arrested by the Hawks for allegedly stealing from a dead man, a disabled man and a homeless woman. Lindile Brian Nompozolo, 52, originally from Mthatha, is charged with three counts of theft totalling more than R1.3-million.He appeared before magistrate Nazeem Joemath in the East London Magistrate s Court on Tuesday to apply for bail.To read more, get a copy of the Daily dispatch or subscribe to our online e-edition.